name: PocketedDeviceImplantationProcedures
title: Pocketed Device Implantation Procedures
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This grouping of value sets identifies patients who have a pocketed device implantation surgical procedure.  These procedures include implantation of drug infusion pumps, pacemakers or implantable defibrillators.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have a pocketed device implantation surgical procedure.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent a surgical procedure to implant a pocketed device such as a drug infusion pump, pacemakers or implantable defibrillators.   Codes used are to be ICD10PCS, ICD9CM or SNOMED-CT codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: None)
